Linde’s Chief Reitzle Gets 12% Pay Increase as Profit Jumps

-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 
2011-03-10T09:39:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/linde-s-chief-reitzle-gets-12-pay-increase-as-profit-jumps.html
  Linde AG (LIN) ’s Chief Executive Officer
Wolfgang Reitzle got a 12 percent increase in compensation for
last year after the company’s net income gained 70 percent.  Reitzle was paid 6.95 million euros ($9.6 million), up from
6.22 million euros the prior year, the Munich-based producer of
industrial gases said today in its  annual report . That included
share options valued at 1.5 million euros in each year. In
addition Linde allocated 1.18 million euros to his pension, down
from 2.05 million euros a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sheenagh Matthews in Frankfurt at 
